My forever childhood memory is I still remembered vividly, the hardships Mama had been through during the years when my dad was fighting his liver cancer. She was the pillar of strength and source of income for the whole family. She never once complained or falter. She supported my sis and I who were then, still studying while taking care of my dad who was frail and weak. Despite having to juggle both work and house chores, she had never once complained, and stayed strong throughout. Whenever my dad felt like giving up, she’d be the one, reading all sorts of books, trying her very best to find means to cure his illness. She’d cook him nutritious meals and make fresh fruit juice everyday even though she was already so exhausted from work. And every night she will spend time to check my homework and ask my progress because she know I am not doing well in school. She’s amazing. 💖 
